author: Matt Scalici | mscalici@al.com
title: Big wins propel Alabama, Florida upward in latest AL.com SEC Power Poll
text:
A big weekend for the Alabama Crimson Tide and the Florida Gators sent both teams up the charts in the latest edition of the AL.com SEC Power Poll.
Alabama's 37-10 blowout win over Georgia has left Crimson Tide fans feeling that everything is right in the world again while Ole Miss, who seemed on the top of the world weeks ago after toppling the Tide, is reeling after a 38-10 loss to Florida and its first year head coach Jim McElwain.
The Tide and Gators will have to stay on their toes this weekend as they face SEC competition in Arkansas and Missouri, respectively.
LSU made its way to the top of the poll this week despite a less than convincing performance against Eastern Michigan. LSU will host South Carolina this weekend in a game that was originally scheduled to be played in Columbia but moved due to flooding in the area.
This week's AL.com SEC Power Poll, with first-place votes in parentheses:
LSU, 5-0 (3) Alabama, 4-1 (2) Texas A&M, 5-0 (1) Florida, 5-0 Ole Miss, 4-1 Georgia, 4-1 Mississippi State, 3-2 Arkansas, 2-3 Missouri, 4-1 Tennessee, 2-3 Auburn, 3-2 Kentucky, 4-1 South Carolina, 2-3 Vanderbilt, 2-3
